24TH FEB:

CSS FLEX :

1.	Display flex
2.	Justify-content :  flex-start, flex-end, space- evenly
3.	Align-items : flex- start, flex-end, center, stretch
4.	Ex   Gap:20px; (defines gap between html elements)
5.	Flex direction: row, column, row-reverse, column-reverse (dafault value is row)
6.	Order – it specifies the order
7.	Flex-grow: defines expansion proportion of particular element  (default it is 0)
8.	Flex-shrink :defines collapsion /compression proportion of elements( default value 1)
9.	Flex-basis – it defines the initial size of element (default value is Auto)
Flex-box : 
•	It is the short form of flexible-box
•	It is one-dimensional


EX:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>flexbox</title>
    <style>
        .parent{
            width: 100%;
            height: 100vh;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            justify-content: flex-start;
            align-items: baseline;
            gap: 20px;
        }
        .child{
            height: 200px;
            width: 200px;
            border: 1px solid black;
            color: white;
        }
        .c1{
            background-color: brown;
            order: 1;
        }
        .c2{
            background-color: red;
        }
        .c3{
            background-color: blue;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="parent">
        <div class="child c1">1</div>
        <div class="child c2">2</div>
        <div class="child c3">3</div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>

EX 2:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>flexbox</title>
    <style>
        .parent{
            width: 100%;
            height: 100vh;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: row;
            justify-content: flex-start;
            align-items: baseline;
            gap: 0px;
          
            

        }
        .child{
            height: 200px;
            width: 200px;
            border: 1px solid black;
            color: white;
            flex-basis: 30%;
        }
        .c1{
            background-color: brown;
            order: 1;
            flex-grow: 2;
            flex-shrink: 2;
        }
        .c2{
            background-color: red;
            flex-shrink: 3;
        }
        .c3{
            background-color: blue;

        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="parent">
        <div class="child c1">1</div>
        <div class="child c2">2</div>
        <div class="child c3">3</div>
    
    </div>
</body>
</html>
